    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0001-3516-5871"
abstract: >-
  Methodology preprint describing axiom-explorer, an autonomous LLM-assisted
  experimental harness for systematic cross-search over modern axiomatic seeds
  in mathematics. The harness selects a small set of recent, productive axioms
  from distinct branches, performs bibliometric and formal-state sweeps over
  their pairwise combinations, builds dossiers, and filters candidates against
  four explicit relevance tests. The role of the LLM is constrained by four
  stop rules; a multi-round AI peer-review loop catches errors before any
  human reviewer is approached. One case study is summarised; the full
  case-study synthesis is in a companion preprint.
